review_blob: pours honey orange in color. Aroma of peach syrup.Decent taste but not neary as good as the raspberry. More of a watered down taste but more of a beer taste.
Poured a  ruby plum color. Smokey malt aroma. very pronounced alcohol.,was ok but a bit disappointing as a Scottish Ale. Tough finish. Will try again

Dark amber pour with a malty head. Nutty fruit aroma that comes at at you wonderfully. Flavors composed of cherry,figs and roasted malts. Just outstanding. Hides the high alcohol nicely. Dreamy creamy is all I can say. Slightly behind Rochefort, but not far.
Bottle poured a hazy gold color with a decent whitish head that doesnt last long. Very mild aroma of citrus. Fruity ale flavor. Good sessional brew.
Poured amber gold with a thin whitish head. Balanced hops and malts.  surprisingly good.
Nutty brown color with a caramel colored head. Great nutty caramel taste, with a nicehoppy finish that isnt over whelming. A good brown ale.
beer_name: New Glarus Fat Squirrel Nut Brown Ale

review_blob: Light gold with a minimal white head. Mild malty aroma. Fruity start with a clean finish. Good sessional beer.

2007 bottle poured a pitch black with a motor oil consistency. Thinmalty head that was nonexistent in no time. Aroma of bourbon and chocolate, accompanied by a smokey oak combo. Tastes of bourbon followed by a nutty coffee. Very powerful,  smoothing out as it warmed. Only way to describe this Imperial Stout is fantastic.

poured a golden amber with a nice white head from a 12 oz. bottle. Orangish aroma thats appealing. Moderate carbonation. Slightly sweet flavor, with a nice hoppy balance. Seems more like an IPA rather than a lager. Really enjoyed this .
12 oz. bottle. Poured a very deep black with a craemy head. Rich malty aroma. Tasted of nutty chocolate.Smooth finish.
Golden amber with a minimal white head.Hoppy citrus aroma. Smooth and very drinkable.

12 oz. bottle poured at home. Pours an orangy amber with an off white head that dissapates quickly. orange hoppy aroma. A wellbalanced ale that finishes very smoothly. probably soon to become one of my favs.
Poured a reddish amber with a nice head that stood up well.Sweet smoky flavor, finishing with a malty, nutty after taste. Really loved it!
Cask offering a deep amber color with a bubbly porous head. Hoppy aroma.Finished much better than it started.
Pours a cooper red color. Nice creamy head that stands up well. Fruity aroma, very pleasing.sweet flavor with a hoppy overtone. Gotta like this!
Golden color with a nice creamy head from the widget can. looked better than it tasted. Ok, but nothing special.
Widget can produces a copper colored body with a substantial creamy head. Great caramel aroma. Very smooth maltyflavor with a slight bitterness at the finish. Hope to drink many more of these
Nice amber body with creamy long lasting head as one would expect from a widget can.Malty aroma. Smooth finish, very drinkable beer.
Tart cherry aroma experienced after the dark red pour. Decent head. Initial taste seems sweet at first, but finishes with a pleasant tartness. Enjoyable
Dark red pour with a pinkish head. aroma really sweet and fruity.Kind of a shock at first taste, very tart but finished wonderfully. This beer grows on you.
Poured a dark amber, accompanied by a nice white head. Slighty bitter but finishes well. Worth drinking again.
Clear golden amber pour with a decent white head. Clean and well balanced. Look forward to my next one.
This beer pours a rich golden brown with a luscious creamy tan head. Wonderful fruity aroma with a spectacular complex flavor. My new favorite!
